STM32 simulation framework using C++ 17.
Just add your project in "projects" section and run it to test logic.


🔌 GPIO Responsibility
    Controls digital pins: HIGH/LOW
    Used for LEDs, buttons, etc.
    Operates at bit level

📡 UART Responsibility
    Sends/receives serial data
    Used for logging, PC communication
    Operates at byte/stream level

🛠️ Together:
    GPIO changes state (e.g., LED), UART reports it (e.g., debug log).


Project Structure:

    stm32_sim_framework/
    │
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    ├── include/
    │   └── hal/
    │       ├── gpio.hpp
    │       ├── uart.hpp
    │       ├── timer.hpp
    │       ├── adc.hpp
    │       ├── i2c.hpp
    │       ├── spi.hpp
    │       └── rcc.hpp
    │
    ├── src/
    |   ├── CMakeLists.txt
    │   ├── main.cpp
    │   └── hal/
    │       ├── gpio.cpp
    │       ├── uart.cpp
    │       ├── timer.cpp
    │       ├── adc.cpp
    │       ├── i2c.cpp
    │       ├── spi.cpp
    │       └── rcc.cpp
    │
    ├── projects/
    │   └── example_project/
    │       ├── CMakeLists.txt
    │       └── main.cpp
